As you can see, even though the *Content.html* content is fully responsive (*div#ScrolledArea* has `overflow: scroll` set) and the iframe width is 100% the iframe still takes the full width of the *div#ScrolledArea* as if the overflow does not even exist. [Demo](http://www.idra.pri.ee/sample/IframeIsolationTest/)

In cases like this, were the `iframe`content has scrolling areas on it, the question becomes, how to get the `iframe` responsive, when the iframe content has horizontally scrolling areas? The problem here is not in the fact that the *Content.html* is not responsive, but in the fact that the iOS Safari simply resizes the iframe so that the `div#ScrolledArea` would be fully visible.

